          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " seem to never sleep, and that’s especially true when it comes to buying vehicles on the internet. Since a car is the second most expensive purchase most people will ever make, for those looking to separate you from a bunch of money quickly, it’s an area where many dishonest people ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "work hard at swindling",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/another-car-selling-scam/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". The Better Business Bureau in Minnesota and North Dakota recently raised the alarm about some disturbing scams.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Learn more about the difference between a good deal and a scam ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 1,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "here",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/difference-good-deal-scam/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "One involved a person who was going to pay $41,300 for a 1963 Chevy Impala from a dealer called Easy Classic Cars. According to the BBB, it was a “bogus” classic car dealer with an address in Minnesota. It advised the shopper to not send any money and instead look for a car through a legitimate dealer.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The BBB also created a business profile for Easy Classic Cars and put a warning on it for all to see. This is why we recommend checking a dealer’s BBB page before proceeding with a transaction. And the same goes for car transport services as well as auto shops.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Too often people believe any listing on Facebook Marketplace, eBay, Craigslist, etc. While those platforms might do some work to weed out scammers, you need to look at everything with a skeptical eye. That’s especially true if you find an unbelievable deal, something scammers do to get you excited and not thinking.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A clear red flag for a vehicle scam is when you’re told to pay a supposed independent third party, often called an escrow service, says the BBB. The problem is this is a way to get your money while the car is never sent.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As the BBB points out, a lot of scammers are creating websites for these escrow companies by using the name and address of real businesses. This is a way to lower your suspicion of a scam.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "While sob stories about military deployment, death in the family, and other tragedies to explain the low price of a car is one red flag, the BBB points out others. A big one is the insistence you use an escrow and pay using a wire transfer instead of something more easily traced like a credit card or cashier’s check.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Ultimately, the more information you can find out about anyone selling you a vehicle online the better before you hand over any money.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Image via Facebook",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
